Three times last week, Donald Trump defied expert advice and touted anecdotal evidence that the anti-malaria drug chloroquine might cure Covid-19.
“They kept saying that it was approved for other things and, you know, Trump kept saying it was basically pretty much a cure.”Woman in ICU: "Trump kept saying it was basically pretty much a cure."
“Drug cleared by Trump, FDA for coronavirus testing also found in fish tanks,” Fox told its readers.
According to a non-peer-reviewed draft paper posted online last week, Raoult and his colleagues began treating 26 Covid-19 patients with hydroxychloroquine earlier this month.
As AFP reported on Wednesday, the Chinese study, published in the Journal of Zhejiang University, involved treating half of a group of 30 Covid-19 patients with hydroxychloroquine for seven days.